The paper deals with the problem of identifying the impulse response of a linear time invariant (LTI) dynamical system, which is a topic in control theory and system identification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses regularization in a Reproducing Kernel Hilbert Space (RKHS), which is a common technique in machine learning and statistical learning theory. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with constructing and characterizing families of kernels, which is a topic in numerical analysis and computational mathematics, suggesting that the paper could also be relevant to categories such as cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
